  <body>
  <br>Do you want to know how to make <i> the best </i> macaroni and cheese? 
    I don't mean your average mac, I mean <b> bomb.com </b> mac and cheese;
    The kind that has actual spice and several kinds of cheese. 
    If that sounds like it is up your alley, then you have found <i> the </i> recipe.
    This recipe will make about 4 servings, so it will definitely feed your family,
    or at the very least, you will have seconds for yourself. 
   </body>
  
  <h2> <u> Ingrediants Needed </u> </h2>
  <li> 2lbs of 93% lean ground hamburger 
  <li> <font size="2"><sup>1</sup>/<sub>2</sub></font> cup of shredded montery jack cheese
  <li> <font size="2"><sup>1</sup>/<sub>2</sub></font> cup of shredded sharp cheddar cheese
        <li> 1 cup of shredded asadero cheese
          
         <br> <i>(If you're too lazy to grab all of these, you can opt to buy three 
          bags of the mexican blend cheese from your local grocery store. I reccommend 
          three if you would like to add extra cheese to bake on top)</i> </b>
<li> 1 tablespoon of flour
  <li> 1 tablespoon of butter
    <li> Adobo
      <li> Chili powder
        <li> Red pepper flakes
          <li>Keyan Pepper
            <li> Garlic Powder
              <li> 1lb of macaroni
                
